; SPDX-License-Identifier: PMPL-1.0-or-later
; INTENT.contractile — Purpose and scope for paint-type
; Helps LLM/SLM agents understand what this repo IS and IS NOT.
;
; Part of the contractile family: MUST, TRUST, DUST, INTENT, ADJUST

; ── Definitions ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
;
; INTENT (noun)
;   The purpose contractile. Defines what this repository IS, what it is
;   NOT (anti-purpose), and which architectural decisions are load-bearing.
;
; ── End Definitions ──────────────────────────────────────────────

(intent-contractile
  (version "1.0.0")
  (repo "paint-type")

  ; === Purpose (what this repo IS) ===
  (purpose
    "paint-type is a cross-platform open-source image editor in the spirit of Paint.NET — capable enough for real work, simple enough to reach for without thinking. It provides a high-dynamic-range (RGBA16F) canvas, a non-destructive layer model, a plugin system, and optional real-time collaboration via Burble WebRTC. The image engine (Ephapax) is written in Rust with linear types; the ABI bridge is formally verified in Idris2 and implemented in Zig; the desktop shell is Gossamer."
  )

  ; === Anti-Purpose (what this repo is NOT — prevents scope creep) ===
  (anti-purpose
    "paint-type is NOT a general-purpose graphics library — image processing APIs belong in Ephapax, not here. It is NOT a plugin runtime — the WASM sandbox is part of paint-type, but individual plugins live in separate repos. It is NOT a web application — Gossamer is the desktop shell, and the web UI runs inside it, not in a browser. It is NOT an animation tool — video and frame-by-frame animation are out of scope for v1.0. It does NOT implement its own WebRTC — that is delegated to Burble. It does NOT implement its own service discovery — that is delegated to Groove."
  )

  ; === Key Architectural Decisions That Must Not Be Reversed ===
  (architectural-invariants
    ("Idris2 for ABI definitions — dependent types prove pointer non-nullability, layout correctness, and FFI safety")
    ("Zig for FFI bridge — zero-cost C ABI, no hidden allocations, no GC pauses")
    ("Rust with linear types for Ephapax — no aliased mutable tile access")
    ("Gossamer as desktop shell — linearly-typed webview, not Electron or native widgets")
    ("AffineScript → typed-wasm for the bridge layer — generated from Idris2 ABI definitions")
    ("RGBA16F tile format, 64x64 tiles — HDR-capable, GPU-friendly, no lossy conversion")
    ("CRDT-compatible tile merging for collaboration — no last-write-wins")
    ("Plugin code never touches Ephapax directly — always through the typed-wasm API surface")
  )

  ; === Sensitive Areas (if in doubt, ask) ===
  (ask-before-touching
    "src/interface/Abi/ — formal proofs; changes require re-verification with idris2 --check"
    "src/interface/ffi/ — C ABI boundary; changes affect all language bindings"
    "src/paint_core/src/lib.rs — tile primitive and linear type invariants"
    ".machine_readable/ — checkpoint files; format is specified"
    ".github/workflows/ — CI gate; changes need explicit approval"
  )

  ; === Ecosystem Position ===
  (ecosystem
    (belongs-to "palimpsest / hyperpolymath estate")
    (depends-on ("gossamer" "ephapax" "burble" "groove" "proven"))
    (depended-on-by ())
  )
)
